@Bob Claster years ago, just as my younger sister was walking out the front door to go see The Sixth Sense at the local AMC, I called out to her, “Bruce Willis’s character is actually dead”.

My sister was positively livid and complained about that incident for years to follow, and I pray that death is truly the end, lest I should be made to stand before some god and account for what I did in 1999.

Nevertheless, I can type this comment without the slightest compunction, as I’m confident that 25 years is well past the statute of limitations for movie spoilers…

